@arams &lsquo;Name for argument of type [java.lang.Long] not specified, and parameter name information not available via reflection. Ensure that the compiler uses the &lsquo;-parameters&rsquo; flag.&rsquo;
This error in a Spring Boot application indicates that Spring Data JPA is unable to map the parameters in your repository method to the query because it cannot retrieve parameter names through reflection.
By default, Java does not retain method parameter names in the compiled bytecode unless you explicitly instruct the compiler to do so using the -parameters flag.
Spring relies on parameter names to match method parameters to query parameters (e.g., @Param(&quot;id&quot;) in a query). If it cannot retrieve the parameter names, it throws this error.

